@AkshayBajajML, it looks like you were having an issue getting this CSS rule to take effect? That's why you had to use const toggleIcon={ fontSize: '14px' }; below?
It can tricky getting your CSS styles to override what's being applied in a third-party component, but I think you can get this CSS rule to work with the following:
font-size: 14px !important;
(At least I see that working for me.)
Then you can 1) remove the const toggleIcon={ fontSize: '14px' };, 2) remove the style={toggleIcon} from the Icon component, and 3) add className={styles.toggleIcon} to the Icon component.
